+/// THE FLEET WORKS — pulse-coupled heartbeat sync over TN (Mirollo–Strogatz).
+/// Each board runs a phase oscillator (period `HB_PERIOD_MS`). When the phase
+/// reaches 1 it FIRES: beats the LED and broadcasts an R2-WIRE `Heartbeat` frame
+/// to the peer. On receiving the peer's fire it nudges its phase forward
+/// (advance-only) — so independent boards converge to beating IN SYNC. The same
+/// task still routes `Event` frames through the `RouteEngine` (deliver/dedup,
+/// field.lab). Boards start deliberately out of phase to show convergence.
